cs.LO, cs.FL, cs.DB, cs.DS, cs.PL 

The paper deals with decidability and complexity results for automata on data trees, which are a type of structured data. This falls under the category of formal languages and automata theory (cs.FL) and logic in computer science (cs.LO). The use of data trees also connects to databases (cs.DB) and data structures (cs.DS). Finally, the paper mentions results related to the XPath query language, which falls under programming languages (cs.PL).
